-- LUST_VS_LOVE - Reflection blocks (6)
('reflection', 'It sounds like you''re trying to figure out whether what you feel is attraction, connection, or something deeper, and that confusion is really challenging.', ARRAY['lust_vs_love', 'confusion', 'feelings'], ARRAY['confused', 'curious'], 1, 50, true),
('reflection', 'When you''re trying to distinguish between lust and love, it can make you question your own feelings and whether you can trust what you''re experiencing.', ARRAY['lust_vs_love', 'trust', 'self_doubt'], ARRAY['confused', 'worried'], 2, 50, true),
('reflection', 'It sounds like part of you is drawn to the intensity and excitement, but another part wonders if there''s something more meaningful underneath, and that conflict is really difficult.', ARRAY['lust_vs_love', 'conflict', 'meaning'], ARRAY['confused', 'curious'], 2, 50, true),
('reflection', 'Trying to sort out lust from love can make you question whether your feelings are real or just physical attraction, and that uncertainty is really unsettling.', ARRAY['lust_vs_love', 'uncertainty', 'feelings'], ARRAY['confused', 'worried'], 2, 50, true),
('reflection', 'It sounds like you''re wondering if the intensity you feel is sustainable or if it''s just the excitement of something new, and that question is really important to explore.', ARRAY['lust_vs_love', 'intensity', 'sustainability'], ARRAY['curious', 'worried'], 2, 50, true),
('reflection', 'When physical attraction is strong, it can be hard to see whether there''s emotional connection underneath, and that confusion can make decisions feel really difficult.', ARRAY['lust_vs_love', 'attraction', 'connection'], ARRAY['confused', 'curious'], 2, 50, true),

-- LUST_VS_LOVE - Normalization blocks (6)
('normalization', 'Trying to figure out whether you feel lust or love is really common, especially in the early stages of a relationship or when physical attraction is strong. That confusion is normal and doesn''t mean you''re doing something wrong.', ARRAY['lust_vs_love', 'normal', 'common'], ARRAY['relieved', 'confused'], 1, 50, true),
('normalization', 'Lust and love aren''t mutually exclusive—you can feel both, and many healthy relationships have strong physical attraction alongside emotional connection. The question is whether there''s more than just the physical.', ARRAY['lust_vs_love', 'both', 'understanding'], ARRAY['relieved', 'confused'], 2, 50, true),
('normalization', 'It''s common to mistake intense physical attraction for love, especially when the chemistry is really strong. That intensity can feel like love, but love usually involves more than just attraction—it involves connection, care, and wanting the other person''s well-being.', ARRAY['lust_vs_love', 'intensity', 'understanding'], ARRAY['confused', 'reflective'], 2, 50, true),
('normalization', 'Some people find that physical attraction fades over time, and what''s left reveals whether there was real connection underneath. That process can be clarifying, even though it can also be disappointing if the attraction was all there was.', ARRAY['lust_vs_love', 'time', 'clarity'], ARRAY['reflective', 'worried'], 2, 50, true),
('normalization', 'It''s normal to question your feelings when you''re trying to distinguish between lust and love. That questioning shows you''re thinking critically about your experience, which is actually a good thing.', ARRAY['lust_vs_love', 'questioning', 'self_awareness'], ARRAY['reflective', 'confused'], 2, 50, true),
('normalization', 'Love often grows over time and deepens with connection, while lust can be more immediate and intense but may not deepen in the same way. Both are valid experiences, but they serve different purposes in relationships.', ARRAY['lust_vs_love', 'understanding', 'time'], ARRAY['reflective', 'confused'], 2, 50, true),

-- LUST_VS_LOVE - Exploration blocks (7)
('exploration', 'When you think about this person, what comes up for you? Physical attraction, emotional connection, care for their well-being, or a combination?', ARRAY['lust_vs_love', 'feelings', 'awareness'], ARRAY['reflective', 'curious'], 1, 50, true),
('exploration', 'What do you think you''d feel if the physical attraction faded? Would there still be something meaningful there?', ARRAY['lust_vs_love', 'sustainability', 'meaning'], ARRAY['reflective', 'curious'], 2, 50, true),
('exploration', 'How do you feel when you''re not with this person? Do you miss them, think about them, care about their life, or is it more about the physical connection?', ARRAY['lust_vs_love', 'connection', 'feelings'], ARRAY['reflective', 'curious'], 2, 50, true),
('exploration', 'What would it look like if this were love? What would be different from what you''re experiencing now?', ARRAY['lust_vs_love', 'vision', 'understanding'], ARRAY['reflective', 'curious'], 2, 50, true),
('exploration', 'How has this experience changed how you think about attraction, connection, and what you want in relationships?', ARRAY['lust_vs_love', 'growth', 'understanding'], ARRAY['reflective', 'hopeful'], 2, 50, true),
('exploration', 'What do you think you need to figure out to feel clear about what this is? Time, more connection, something else?', ARRAY['lust_vs_love', 'clarity', 'needs'], ARRAY['reflective', 'confused'], 2, 50, true),
('exploration', 'If you could give yourself advice about this situation, what would you want to remember?', ARRAY['lust_vs_love', 'wisdom', 'self'], ARRAY['compassionate', 'reflective'], 2, 50, true),

-- LUST_VS_LOVE - Reframe blocks (4)
('reframe', 'Lust and love can coexist, and many healthy relationships have both strong physical attraction and deep emotional connection. The question isn''t whether you feel lust—it''s whether there''s more than just lust. Love usually involves wanting the other person''s well-being, caring about them as a person, and feeling connected beyond just the physical. If you find yourself thinking about them when you''re apart, caring about their life and feelings, and wanting to support them, that''s often a sign there''s more than just attraction.', ARRAY['lust_vs_love', 'understanding', 'connection'], ARRAY['reflective', 'hopeful'], 2, 50, true),
('reframe', 'Physical attraction is often immediate and intense, while love tends to grow over time as you get to know someone and build connection. If what you''re feeling is mostly about the physical and the excitement, it might be lust. But if you find yourself wanting to know them deeper, caring about their well-being, and feeling connected even when you''re not together, that''s often a sign of something more. Time and deeper connection can help clarify what you''re really feeling.', ARRAY['lust_vs_love', 'time', 'connection', 'clarity'], ARRAY['reflective', 'hopeful'], 2, 50, true),
('reframe', 'There''s nothing wrong with feeling lust or strong physical attraction—it''s a normal and valid part of human experience. The question is whether you want more than just that. If you''re looking for a deeper connection, then it''s worth exploring whether that''s possible with this person. But if you''re okay with just the physical connection and that''s what both people want, that''s also valid. What matters is being honest with yourself and the other person about what you want and what you''re experiencing.', ARRAY['lust_vs_love', 'honesty', 'needs', 'validity'], ARRAY['reflective', 'hopeful'], 2, 50, true),
('reframe', 'Sometimes the intensity of physical attraction can make it hard to see whether there''s emotional connection underneath. If you''re unsure, it can help to spend time together doing things that aren''t just physical—talking, sharing experiences, getting to know each other as people. That can reveal whether there''s real connection or if it''s mostly about the attraction. Love usually deepens with connection and time, while lust may stay intense but not necessarily deepen in the same way.', ARRAY['lust_vs_love', 'connection', 'time', 'clarity'], ARRAY['reflective', 'hopeful'], 2, 50, true);

